<SLUG> BC-BBA-RANGER-SIDER-TEX </SLUG>
 DEFENSE HELPS SELE SETTLE DOWN (For use by
NYTimes News Service clients) By DONALD EMMONS c.1998 Fort Worth
Star-Telegram
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; P &QR; ARLINGTON, Texas Q The evening started out precariously for
Rangers
right-hander Aaron Sele last night.  &QL; P &QR; He gave up two runs on two
hits in the first inning against the Chicago
White Sox and appeared on his way to remaining winless in seven
outings since the All-Star break.  &QL; P &QR; However, Sele settled down as
the Rangers rolled to a 12-3 drubbing of the
White Sox before 28,175 at The Ballpark in Arlington.  &QL; P &QR; RI
struggled a little bit early, but I kind of gritted my teeth and
came
back and pitched well,S said Sele, who earned his 13th decision of
the year, tying a career high for a season. RIt was just a matter
of making some changes to get the ball down.S  &QL; P &QR; Sele (13-8)
pitched eight innings, allowing three runs on 10 hits while
striking out two and walking two. After allowing the White Sox to
score another run in the second, he had little trouble the rest of
the game, until he was replaced after throwing 110 pitches, 78 of
them strikes.  &QL; P &QR; The decision ended an 0-3 showing over four games
for Sele, who hadnUt won
since July 4. It also helped to restore his earned-run-average that
had ballooned to 4.51 over his previous six outings.  &QL; P &QR; RAaron
bounced back after struggling with his command in the first and
second innings,S Rangers manager Johnny Oates said. RAfter that, I
thought he made a lot of quality pitches.S  &QL; P &QR; However, Oates
considered SeleUs first victory in nearly a month a product
of sound pitching and a sure-gloved defense inspired by two
newcomers Q third baseman Todd Zeile and shortstop Royce Clayton.
 &QL; P &QR; Acquired in trades, Zeile and Clayton each made fielding plays
that helped
kill potential early scoring opportunities for the White Sox.  &QL; P &QR; RI
think our pitcher saw a couple of plays [by Zeile and Clayton] made
tonight that gave him confidence,S Oates said. RThe pitchers see we
can take care of the ball and score some runs. That can spread all
over.  &QL; P &QR; R[Sele] started getting the ball down.S
 &QL; P &QR; Sele, who said he never got down on himself during the recent
winless
period, also credited his defensive support Q particularly a
revamped left side of the infield Q for the win.  &QL; P &QR; RI was happy
that the first inning didnUt turn into a bigger inning [for
the White Sox],S Sele said. RI was able to stay out there and they
did the rest.S
</P>
