<HEADER>
A4666 &Cx1f; ttx-z
r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BBA-RANGERS-WHITE-SOX     08-03 0640
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BBA-RANGERS-WHITE-SOX-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
ZEILE, RANGERS RIP WHITE SOX
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SIMON GONZALEZ 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   ARLINGTON, Texas _ The Rangers wanted to upgrade at shortstop
and in the rotation, so they traded for Royce Clayton and Todd
Stottlemyre.
</P>
<P>
   Todd Zeile, the other guy general manager Doug Melvin brought in
during the Friday trading frenzy? Oh yeah, part of the cost for
Clayton and Stottlemyre was Fernando Tatis, so the team needed a
third baseman.
</P>
<P>
   So far, the ``other guy'' is the best guy.
</P>
<P>
   Zeile reached base in all five plate appearances and made all
the plays in the field yesterday as the Rangers thumped the Chicago
White Sox, 12-3, at The Ballpark in Arlington to reclaim sole
possession of first place in the American League West.
</P>
<P>
   Zeile walked three times, hit his second home run in two games,
and had another homer taken away when White Sox right fielder
Magglio Ordonez brought it back in the park and ``held'' him to a
double.
</P>
<P>
   ``Look at what Todd Zeile's done getting on base,'' manager
Johnny Oates said. ``And he's played some mighty fine third base
both nights.''
</P>
<P>
   He is 5-for-6 _ a sparkling .833 average _ with two homers, four
runs batted in, four runs scored and three walks in his first two
games in a Texas uniform.
</P>
<P>
   ``I couldn't be happier, starting off the way I have,'' Zeile
said. ``To see two wins since I've been here is great. I think
everyone is energized.''
</P>
<P>
   Indeed, good things also are happening for the lineup as a
whole. The Rangers had 17 hits last night, including homers by
Zeile, Roberto Kelly, Lee Stevens and Rusty Greer. The first eight
hits and seven runs came off White Sox starter Jaime Navarro
(8-13).
</P>
<P>
   Aaron Sele (13-8) benefited from the booming bats to win for the
first time since July 4. He gave the offense a chance to put it
away by pitching six shutout innings after giving up two runs in
the first.
</P>
<P>
   Sele didn't have to be that good, because the offense has come
out of a collective slump. The Rangers have 29 hits and six homers
in the last two games.
</P>
<P>
   Those are, of course, the first two games since the new players
joined the team.
</P>
<P>
   ``The last two days have been a lot of fun,'' Oates said.
``Maybe the new guys are trying to impress us, and maybe the old
guys are trying to impress the new guys.''
</P>
<P>
   Actually, the most impressive moment last night was the home run
that Stevens hit in the third inning. He turned on a fastball by
Navarro and clubbed it far and deep down the right-field line.
</P>
<P>
   The only question was whether it would be fair or foul. Stevens
tried to influence it by leaning to the left as he trotted toward
first.
</P>
<P>
   ``I was trying to keep it fair a little bit,'' Stevens said.
</P>
<P>
   The ball hit the foul pole, about five feet from the top. If it
wasn't still going up, it had barely started coming down. It was
measured at 385 feet, the distance from the plate to where it hit
the pole. If it hadn't been stopped, it might have carried another
100 feet.
</P>
<P>
   A little higher and to the left, and Stevens might have hit the
``win a free suit'' sign.
</P>
<P>
   Stevens also singled in the eighth, and is 7-for-12 in his last
four games to come out of a deep slump.
</P>
<P>
   Baseball being what it is, Stevens and his slumping teammates
surely would have broken out sooner or later. After all, this is a
team that leads the majors in runs scored.
</P>
<P>
   That the surge happened when Oates began putting Zeile and
Clayton in the lineup is more than a coincidence, though. Zeile
replaced Tatis, who had three homers in 95 games, and Clayton _ who
had two hits yesterday _ replaced Kevin Elster, who was hitting in
the .230s.
</P>
<P>
   ``There's no doubt in my mind we improved our lineup on a
consistent basis,'' Oates said.
</P>
<P>
   The biggest improvement so far is the ``other guy.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-08-03-98 0057EDT &QL; 
