   VILLAGE-MEDIA (New York) _ iVillage.com began with little more
than the premise ``Internet for the rest of us'' and a focus on
baby boomers. After encountering its share of false starts (like a
site, ``Vices and Virtues,'' now defunct, about the competing
forces of indulgence and health), it has evolved into the leading
women's online ``community'' on the Web. It attracted more than 2
million different visitors during June, according to the Web
measurement company Relevant Knowledge. By Lisa Napoli. (With photo
and graphic.)
