   CULTURE
</P>
<P>
   (Moved in `e' category)
</P>
<P>
   GUGGENHEIM-HOGS (New York) _ ``The Art of the Motorcycle'' is an
exhibition quite different from anything else that Museum Mile on
Fifth Avenue has ever experienced. Bathed in biker glory, it has
become the most highly attended exhibition in the Guggenheim's
61-year history, far outstripping retrospectives of Roy
Lichtenstein and Ellsworth Kelly, and more popular than
authoritative surveys of Chinese, Russian and Italian art. By Carol
Vogel. (With photos.)
</P>
<P>
   CUNNINGHAM-DANCE-REVIEW (New York) _ Pure movement has seemed
Merce Cunningham's primary concern over 45 years of making dances
for his company. It is a concern reflected in the programs'
earliest choreography, created in 1956, in the new work on the
program and in his latest explorations of computer dance, the
subject of a panel discussion and video installation that were also
part of this dance-packed weekend at Jacob's Pillow. By Jennifer
Dunning. (With photo.)
