<HEADLINE>
`COUSINE' IS MARVELOUS; `QUICKSILVER' HAS ZEST 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.1998 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES:  &UR; ``Cousin Cousine''  &LR; _ Jean-Charles Tacchella's
1975 French comedy is a marvelous recollection of wispy Gallic
romance at its best. Marie-Christine Barrault's breezy sexiness
sets the tone for a movie about infidelity that's remarkably
faithful to its aesthetic parameters.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ``Quicksilver Highway'' &LR;  _ Christopher Lloyd stars as a bizarre
storyteller who weaves two horrifying tales in this surprisingly
effective chiller. Beware of graphic scenes, but it's a terrific
find. While the stories are visually engaging, it's Lloyd's
old-fashioned monologues that gives ``Quicksilver'' its zest.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ``Jackie Brown''  &LR; _ Quentin Tarantino's homage to the
blaxploitation films of the '70s hits all the right notes but
mostly at the wrong time. Rent ``Foxy Brown'' instead.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ``Blues Brothers 2000''  &LR; _ The Blues Brothers without John
Belushi? C'mon. It's like Laurel without Hardy or Abbott without
Costello. Forget it.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ``Deceiver'' &LR;  _ A fine cast including Tim Roth, Chris Penn,
Renee Zellweger, Michael Rooker, Ellen Burstyn, and Rosanna
Arquette is wasted in the set-bound police procedural. The plot
meanders.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
---- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS:  &UR; Aug. 11:  &LR; ``The Man in the Iron Mask,''
``Mr. Nice Guy,'' ``Senseless,'' ``1776,'' ``John and Julie,'' ``I
Love You, I Love You Not,'' ``Godspell,'' ``Three for the Show,''
``The Informant,'' ``The Big Lebowski,'' ``Niagra, Niagra,'' ``Mr.
Nice Guy,'' ``The All New Captain Kangaroo,'' ``The Subsitute 2:
School's Out,'' ``Elvis Meets Nixon,'' ``Hamsun,'' ``Merlin.''
 &UR; Aug. 18:  &LR; ``The Apostle,'' ``Kundun,'' ``An Alan Smithee Film:
Burn Hollywood Burn,'' ``A Sunday in the Country,'' ``The
Clockmaker,'' ``A Self Made Hero,'' ``Summer Fling,'' ``The
Borrowers.''  &UR; Aug. 25:  &LR; ``The Leading Man,'' ``Men With Guns,''
``The Last Way Out,'' ``Sub Down,'' North Shore Fish,''
``Pocahontas: Journey to a New World,'' ``Naked Lies.''  &UR; Sept. 1:
 &LR; ``Titanic,'' ``Absolutely Fabulous Moments,'' ``Barney's Great
Adventure: The Movie,'' ``Star Trek: The Next Generation,'' ``The
Spooktacular New Adventures of Casper,'' ``Leviathan,'' ``The Vicar
of Dibley,'' ``Phantasm.'' &UR; Sept. 8:  &LR; ``Primary Colors,'' ``A Call
to Remember,'' ``Children of the Noisy Village,'' ``I Love You ...
Don't Touch Me.''  &UR; Sept. 15:  &LR; ``Lady and the Tramp,'' ``He Got
Game,'' ``Eat, Drink, Man, Woman,'' ``Suicide Kings,'' ``Man With
the Gun,'' ``To Live.''
</P>
</TEXT>
