<P>
   MISSILE _ In the controversy over whether sensitive technology
was transferred to China following a crash of a commercial
satellite in the winter of 1996, Republicans have blamed the
Clinton Administration for weakening controls on the export of
commercial satellites by giving the business-friendly Commerce
Department the power to approve satellite licenses. But documents
provided by the White House to the various congressional committees
investigating the matter show that Republicans were pushing for the
very same changes behind the scenes. In fact, one document
indicates that Michael Armstrong, former CEO of Hughes Electronics
Corp. and head of a presidential panel on exports, told White House
officials that he had the support of House Speaker Newt Gingrich.
(Carr, Cox News Service).
