<P>
   HIV-MEDICARE (Washington) _ Sixty-eight House members, including
Rep. Nancy Pelosi and House Minority Leader Richard A. Gephardt ask
Health Secretary Donna Shalala to define people with HIV as
``disabled'' so they can qualify for Medicaid and obtain expensive
drugs that can delay the onset of AIDS. By JUDY HOLLAND.
</P>
<P>
   SOCIAL-SECURITY (Washington) _ Martha Phillips, director of the
Concord Coalition, a bipartisan group that lobbies for a balanced
budget, says lawmakers have a rare opportunity to fix Social
Security. Times are good, she notes, and President Clinton
understands the problems of the system and wants to avoid deficit
spending. By NICOLE TSONG.
</P>
