   &UR; INTERNATIONAL &LR;  (``i'' code)
</P>
<P>
   CONGO-FIGHTING (Abidjan) _ An army rebellion has broken out in
Congo; the Kabila government declares an overnight curfew in
Kinshasa; sources say Foreign Minister Bizima Karaha and
Presidential Affairs Minister Deogratias Bugera, both ethnic Tutsi,
have fled the country. By Howard W. French.
</P>
<P>
   MOZAMBIQUE-ECON (Maputo) _ A boom in Maputo is a tiny beginning
in a country that still vies for the title of world's poorest. By
Donald G. McNeil Jr.
</P>
<P>
   COLOMBIA-U.S. (Washington) _ The president-elect of Colombia
meets with Clinton, Albright and McCaffrey. By Diana Jean Schemo.
</P>
<P>
   MIDEAST-TALKS (Jerusalem) _ Apparently in an effort to rescue
imperiled peace talks, Israel is reported to be preparing to
release dozens of Palestinian prisoners whose release had been
urged by Palestinian negotiators. By Douglas Jehl.
</P>
<P>
   KASHMIR-TERROR (New Delhi) _ Suspected Kashmiri guerrillas kill
34 villagers in an attack in the state of Himachal Pradesh.
</P>
<P>
   INDONESIA-PROBE (Jakarta) _ Indonesia's military begins an
investigation into the kidnappings and torture of dozens of
political activists and the suspected involvement of the military,
including Lt. Gen. Prabowo Subianto, former President Suharto's
son-in-law.
</P>
