daytime jobs, nights vamping in dresses. By Ralph Blumenthal.
</P>
<P>
   SEATTLE-NAZI-ART (Undated) _ The heirs of Paul Rosenberg, a
prominent Jewish art dealer who fled Paris for the United States
during World War II, filed suit in federal court against the
Seattle Art Museum to recover a Matisse painting that was
confiscated by the Nazis in 1941. The litigation, the first against
an American museum for art stolen by the Nazis from a Jewish
family, provides an inkling of how complicated it may be to unravel
claims that are just now surfacing, more than a half-century after
the war. By Judith H. Dobrzynski.
</P>
<P>
   BOSTON-ARTHUR (Boston) _ At Boston's Children's Museum, a socko
Arthur the Aardvark show. By Sara Rimer.
</P>
