<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Insider Trading
 &HT;    By Robert Luke
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   The following insider transactions were disclosed in the latest
reporting period.
</P>
<P>
   At Colony Bankcorp, Curtis Summerlin, director, sold 4,400
shares June 2-30 at between $25.75 and $28.75 each, totaling
$122,250. Summerlin now holds 117,269 shares, worth $3,180,922 at
Friday's price of $27.12 1/2 on Nasdaq.
</P>
<P>
   At Georgia-Pacific, Harvey C. Fruehauf, director, indirectly
disposed of by gift 999 shares of Georgia-Pacific Group on June 29
at $57.59 each, totaling $57,532. He also indirectly disposed of by
gift 999 shares of Georgia-Pacific Timber Co. at $22.88 each,
totaling $45,714.
</P>
<P>
   The gifts were to a family member, said Ken Haldin, a
Georgia-Pacific spokesman.
</P>
<P>
   Fruehauf now holds 425,166 Georgia-Pacific Group shares directly
and indirectly, worth $21,842,903 at Friday's price of $51.37 1/2
on the New York Stock Exchange. He also holds 425,166
Georgia-Pacific Timber Co. shares, worth $9,539,662 at Friday's
price of $22.43 3/4.
</P>
