   BRAVES-LIGTENBERG _ Seems the Braves made a pretty good deal for
Kerry Ligtenberg, who has progressed to become the team's closer.
He was obtained for a few bats and balls. (Stinson, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   BRAVES-NOTEBOOK _ ATLANTA _ Inside the Braves' clubhouse.
(Atlanta Journal-Constitution) ETA: 8 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   BRAVES-SIDEBAR _ ATLANTA _ Sidebar on the Braves. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) ETA: 8 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   BRAVES-ONDECK _ ATLANTA _ A brief preview of tomorrow's Braves
game. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   JUNIOR-OLYMPICS-SKI _ Round Rock High School junior Jimmy
Siemers, winner of the United States Junior Olympic Water Ski Team
Trials earlier this month, will represent the U.S. in the Junior
World Championships Aug. 19-23 in Dijon, France. (Rosner, Austin
American-Statesman) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   GEORGE-COLUMN _ MIAMI _ Spill all the Miami Dolphins running
backs out of the bag and search for the basic parts of the killer
running game Jimmy Johnson hopes to build. Clearly, some assembly
is required. Is there something left at the bottom of the bag?
Wait, yes, it's Jerris McPhail, the fastest man on the team, but
whether he qualifies as anything else is another question. (George,
Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   MARIS-RECORD _ Is there something left at the bottom of the bag?
Wait, yes, it's Jerris McPhail, the fastest man on the team, but
whether he qualifies as anything else is a question Jimmy has been
asking himself since spending a fifth-round draft pick on the East
Carolina curiosity two years ago. (Capozzi, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
