   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   MUSIC-BRAIN (Undated) -- Humans aren't the only mammals to
benefit from the famous ``Mozart effect'' _ better performance on
certain intelligence tests after listening to the 18th century
composer's music. So do rats. By Richard A. Knox. 750 words.
</P>
<P>
   GAYS-RESEARCHER (Boston) -- Children's Hospital researcher
lashes out at anti-gay groups, accusing them of misappropriating
his work in national ads claiming that gays can choose to convert
to a straight lifestyle. By Ann E. Kornblut. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   LEWIS-APPRECIATE (Undated) -- TV performers can stay on the tube
for decades, remembered for one character in particular. For Shari
Lewis, who had cancer and died Monday at age 65, that meant Lamb
Chop. By Don Aucoin. 750 words. (a and e coding)
</P>
