   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   POLMONEY-HOUSE _ WASHINGTON _ The results and impact of the
House's roll-call vote Monday evening on the Shays-Meehan
bipartisan campaign finance reform bill. Vote expected between 8
p.m. and 10 p.m. EDT. (Mollison, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   GIFORUM _ WASHINGTON _ Fifty years after it was founded as an
advocacy group for Hispanic veterans, the American G.I. Forum will
take its place alongside other veterans' groups that hold federal
charters. Congress, suspending a 10-year moratorium on charters,
recognized the forum during votes today in the House and Friday in
the Senate. The charter arrives in time for the forum's national
convention and celebration of its founding in Corpus Christi,
Texas. ``It's a good to get what you've been after for 50 years,''
said Gil Rodriguez, outgoing commander of the forum's Austin
chapter. ``It's a good beginning for the second'' 50 years.
(Harlan, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   MISSILE _ In the controversy over whether sensitive technology
was transferred to China following a crash of a commercial
satellite in the winter of 1996, Republicans have blamed the
Clinton Administration for weakening controls on the export of
commercial satellites by giving the business-friendly Commerce
Department the power to approve satellite licenses. But documents
provided by the White House to the various congressional committees
investigating the matter show that Republicans were pushing for the
very same changes behind the scenes. In fact, one document
indicates that Michael Armstrong, former CEO of Hughes Electronics
Corp. and head of a presidential panel on exports, told White House
officials that he had the support of House Speaker Newt Gingrich.
(Carr, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   FARM _ Texas Sen. Phil Gramm announces a plan to speed aid to
farmers affected by the drought. (Mahoney, Austin
American-Statesman). 15.
</P>
<P>
   AFFIRMATIVE-ACTION _ ATLANTA _ A coalition of organizations
(including the NAACP and SCLC) is launching a national movement to
save affirmative action. (Pendered, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   SWITCHED _ BUENA VISTA, Va. _ The mystery of two baby girls
switched at birth in 1995 has taken a further twist with the
discovery that the couple raising one of the girls were killed in a
car crash, knowing nothing of the mix-up. Now, relatives of the man
killed in the July 4 crash say they want his biological daughter
back. And the woman who has been raising the girl whose biological
parents were killed is looking forward to meeting her own
biological daughter. (Manuel, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   FLADEMS _Waves are crashing over the bow of the once-dominant
Florida Democratic Party, which is foundering on the rocks of a
self-inflicted racial controversy that could sink the campaign to
hold onto its last remaining high-profile state office: the
governorship. (MWilliams, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   MORELAND _ New Moreland custody hearing before judge Murphy.
(Hundley, Dayton Daily News).
</P>
