<HEADLINE>
LEWIS REWROTE THE RULES IN A HIGH-TECH MEDIUM 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (a and e coding)   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By DON AUCOIN  
 c.1998 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   As a high-tech medium, television usually requires effects more
special than a talking sock.
</P>
<P>
   But Shari Lewis was so gifted a puppeteer, ventriloquist, and
