u f &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-LADN-BUDGET &LR;      08-03 0204
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LADN-BUDGET </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following business
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Tuesday, Aug. 4, and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact Tom Hicks at the Daily News, (818) 713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   ALBERTSONS-LUCKY (Los Angeles) _ Albertson's Inc. is buying the
parent of Lucky supermarket and Sav-on drugstores for $11.7 billion
in stock and assumed debt, giving the Idaho-based grocer a stronger
foothold in the West. By Deborah Adamson.
</P>
<P>
   SUPERMARKET-SIZE (Los Angeles) _ If you think supermarkets are
big now, just wait. Analysts believe the Albertson's deal will help
pave the way for massive stores selling everything from baked beans
to computers under a single roof. By Dave McNary.
</P>
<P>
   ALBERTSONS-DRUGS (Los Angeles) _ Forget the mega-chain of
grocery stores that will be created by Monday's proposed merger,
the proposed deal would make Albertson's the biggest operator of
drugstores in the Los Angeles area. By Ben Sullivan.
</P>
<P>
   LLOYD-COLUMN (Los Angeles) _ Ken LLoyd, Ph.D., a specialist in
organizational behavior, answers question on getting ahead in or
just staying afloat in today's working world.
</P>
</TEXT>
