<HEADER>
A5883 &Cx1f; taf-z
u l &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BY-DESIGN-FASHION-NYT     08-03 0180
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BY-DESIGN-FASHION-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
BY DESIGN: TIME TO PUT YOUR FOOT DOWN
</HEADLINE>
   (nk) 
 By ANNE-MARIE SCHIRO   
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Flats have outpaced stilettos as the chic shoes for fall.
Designers have chosen them to give a new look to this year's
revival of long skirts, tacitly acknowledging that high heels are
not universally popular as everyday wear.
</P>
<P>
   Ballet flats include Isaac Mizrahi's classic leather version
($220 at Saks Fifth Avenue); Enzo Angiolini's cap-toe in velvet
($72 at Bloomingdale's), and Chanel's cap-toe in leather ($340 at
Saks and Neiman Marcus).
</P>
<P>
   In skimmers, Bloomingdale's has satins by CK Calvin Klein ($130)
and Nicole Miller ($110), and python or velvet from Isaac by Isaac
Mizrahi ($130). The store also has Mary Janes in gray flannel by
Cynthia Rowley ($169) and in velvet by BCBG Max Azria ($145).
</P>
<P>
   Mary Janes by Martinez Valero are at Macy's in leather ($140),
and at the Co-Op at Barneys New York ($175). Skimmers by Silvia
Fiorentina ($340), Ferragamo ($190) and Anne Klein ($160) are all
at Neiman Marcus.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
