   BOEING-MERGER (Seattle) Did the Boeing-McDonnell Douglas merger
contribute to Boeing's current woes? Maybe so, conjecture some
analysts a year after the giant combination. If Phil Condit had
been spending more time monitoring and managing what was going on
on the factory floor, instead of trying to put a deal together,
production snarls might not have beern as bad.
