   QUAKE-NORTHWEST (Seattle) A startling new assessment of
earthquake danger in the Pacific Northwest shows that the Puget
Sound region could be the location of the worst earthquake in
recent time, a 9.5 temblor that would clearly ruin your day. That's
the assessment from Craig Weaver, head of the U.S. Geological
Survey's Seattle office and a leading expert on seismic activity in
the Pacific Northwest. The new assessment was to open a meeting of
top earthquake engineers and scientists about the potential of a
`Big One' and how to minimize risk.
</P>
