<TEXT>
<P>
   (se)
</P>
<P>
   EDITORS: Newspapers that used all or part of the Page 1 New York
Times series last month about a Cuban exile's campaign of violence
aimed at overthrowing Fidel Castro should take note of CUBA-TERROR,
a 900-word story moving by 9 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   The series quoted the exile, Luis Posada Carriles, as saying
that the campaign received financial support from leaders of the
Cuban-American National Foundation, the most influential exile
organization in the United States.
</P>
<P>
   On Sunday, Posada told a television interviewer that he
deliberately lied to The New York Times about the financing.
</P>
<P>
   Tonight's CUBA-TERROR story will detail Carriles' latest
statements, list the additional sources The Times had on the story
and include a statement from Bill Keller, the managing editor of
the paper, that The Times is confident of the veracity of the
original series of articles.
</P>
<P>
   The New York Times News Service
</P>
