<P>
   ATTENTION EDITORS: The following photos are part of tonight's
New York Times Photo Package, moving 8/03/98. Photo clients will
automatically receive these photos via AP's PhotoExpress or may
download them from either the Wieck Photo Database in Dallas at
972-392-0888 or from NYTPhotos on Newscom at 305-448-8411.
Non-clients can make individual purchases by calling 212-556-4204.
</P>
<P>
   (NYT18) WOODBRIDGE, N.Y. -- Aug. 3, 1998 --
CATSKILLS-DANCE-HOST, 8-3 -- ``It's as if I'm a drug and I'm giving
them this high,'' Victor Aviles says of being a dance host. He
danced with Evelyn Meier in the Catskills. While Aviles has had
women put room keys and phone numbers and cash into the pockets of
his white dinner jacket, he sees his job as taking care of the
ladies. ``You have to love it,'' he says. ``You can be taking on an
impossible task.'' (Librado Romero/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT17) WASHINGTON -- Aug. 3, 1998 -- CAMPAIGN-FINANCE, 8-3 --
Staff members of the coalition for the overhaul of campaign
financing meet Monday in the office of Rep. Christopher Shays,
R-Conn., in striped shirt. Rep. Martin Meehan, D-Mass., at left in
white shirt, co-sponsored the bill along with Shays. (Paul
Hosefros/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT16) NEW YORK -- Aug. 3, 1998 -- NY-PORN-SHOPS, 8-3 -- The
sign advertising the Big Top Lounge - part of Show World, the
pornography palace - is taken down Monday. In an attempt to comply
with a new zoning law that prohibits establishments in restricted
areas from having more than 40 percent of their inventories
dedicated to sex, the Big Top Theater upstairs now offers old
movies, not nude entertainment. (John Sotomayor/New York Times
Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT15) LAS VEGAS -- Aug. 3, 1998 -- LAS-VEGAS-MAYOR, 8-3 -- Jan
Jones, left, the mayor of Las Vegas and a Democratic candidate for
governor in Nevada, is undergoing treatment for breast cancer.
Although Ms. Jones says that the surgery she underwent in February
was successful and that the odds that she is cured are better than
90 percent, doctors are still pumping toxins into her body, in case
there is any residual cancer to be vanquished. (Monica Almeida/New
York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT14) LOS ANGELES -- Aug. 3, 1998 -- OBIT-LEWIS-B&AMP;W, 8-3 --
Shari Lewis and Lamb Chop in her Beverly Hills home in 1992. Lewis,
whose estimable skills as a ventriloquist and puppeteer helped her
win 12 Emmy Awards and the hearts of parents and their children for
four decades with a woolly hand puppet named Lamb Chop, died Sunday
in Los Angeles. She was 65 and lived in Beverly Hills. The cause
was cancer, said her spokeswoman, Maggie Begley. (Steve
Goldstein/New York Times Photo) *LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT13) LAGUNA BEACH, Calif. -- Aug. 3, 1998 --
LAGUNA-TRAVEL-LADN-2, 8-3 -- The shoreline vistas in Laguna Beach
are magnificent. Laguna is about 75 miles from the Valley or Los
Angeles, depending on where you live - and an hour and a half drive
on a good traffic day. The scenery here is breathtaking, and you'll
feel like you've been in another world - and away much longer than
you really were. (Natalie Haughton/Los Angeles Daily News Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT12) LAGUNA BEACH, Calif. -- Aug. 3, 1998 --
LAGUNA-TRAVEL-LADN-1, 8-3 -- With homes perched on curving cliffs,
the shoreline vistas in Laguna Beach are magnificent. In this city
long known as an artist colony, there's plenty to take in - surf,
sand, art galleries, shopping, restaurants - and through the end of
August, live performances nightly of the Pageant of the Masters.
(Natalie Haughton/Los Angeles Daily News Photo)
</P>
