<HEADLINE>
SPIELBERG SHOOTS ERNIE'S WAR 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By E.J. MONTINI  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   A long, slow tracking shot in the movie ``Saving Private Ryan''
shows Omaha Beach in the aftermath of the D-Day invasion. It's a
picture of horror and waste and sacrifice, painted in heartbreaking
detail. If you've read the dispatches of Ernie Pyle, you know what
it looked like.
</P>
<P>
   ``The strong, swirling tides of the Normandy coast line shifted
