<HEADLINE>
QUOTATION OF THE DAY
</HEADLINE>
 (Eds.: This quotation refers to BC-NY-COP-SHOT-NYT, which moved in
``a'' news file.) 
c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``I know you can't understand this now, but your father was a
hero. And all those superheroes that I know you like to play with,
even if you put them all together, they would be nothing compared
to what your father meant to all the people in this room.''
</P>
<P>
   _LARRY OLINSKY, a Staten Island, N.Y., police officer, to the
6-year-old son of a slain colleague.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
