<HEADLINE>
USC RECRUIT STILL NOT OUT OF JAM
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ USC football recruit Windrell Hayes will not
report for training camp Wednesday because he continues to face
three felony charges for writing bad checks for merchandise.
</P>
<P>
   Hayes' trial is scheduled for Nov. 16 in Stockton, but if he is
able to plea bargain and reduce the charges to a misdemeanor, the
wide receiver might be able to join the football team.
</P>
<P>
   Hayes has already turned down one offer from the Lodi district
attorney to settle the case, because he would have been responsible
for at least $15,000 in damages to victims.
</P>
<P>
   Head coach Paul Hackett said it is possible a settlement might
be reached within 10 days.
</P>
<P>
   Hayes, a wide receiver, is a transfer from San Jose State.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
