<SLUG> BC-NY-RAPES-ARREST-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MAN CHARGED WITH 4 RAPES IN BRONX 
</HEADLINE>
  (mk) 
 By MICHAEL COOPER   
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ A 28-year-old man suspected of scaling fire escapes
to rape women in the Bronx _ perhaps as many as 11 _ was captured
on Sunday after his attempt at another break-in and rape was
foiled, police said Monday.
</P>
<P>
   The man, Rudolph Moore, was charged Monday with four rapes
involving fire-escape break-ins after four women picked him out of
lineups, said Officer Theresa Farello, a department spokeswoman.
Moore is also a suspect in seven similar rapes during the last
year, she said.
</P>
<P>
   Moore was arrested after he was seen climbing down a fire escape
into a woman's apartment in the Norwood section of the Bronx,
Farello said. Police received a 911 call about a man on a fire
escape on Knox Place, she said, but before officers arrived, the
man had climbed into a third-floor apartment and tried to rape the
woman in front of her two children.
</P>
<P>
   The woman, who was not identified by police because she was the
victim of an attempted rape, broke free and ran down to the street
with her two children, police said. The man escaped over the roof
and down another fire escape to the street, police said.
</P>
<P>
   After police arrived, they called for a large deployment of
officers, and Moore was arrested nearby a short time later, police
said.
</P>
<P>
   Investigators quickly realized that the method of the attack was
familiar, and they began working to determine whether Moore could
be linked to any of the other fire-escape rapes that have plagued
the Bronx in the last year.
</P>
<P>
   Eleven women have been raped there since last August, each
reporting that the attacker climbed into the apartment from a fire
escape. The most recent attack occurred on Wednesday, police said.
All the attacks took place near the Mosholu Parkway, police said.
</P>
<P>
   Because the descriptions of the suspect in the rapes varied
slightly _ in some accounts he was described as a dark-skinned
Hispanic man, in others as an African-American _ police divided the
cases into three distinct patterns to be investigated. Monday,
investigators said that they believed Moore was responsible for all
the attacks.
</P>
<P>
   Moore, who told investigators that he worked as an exotic
dancer, was convicted of first-degree robbery in 1990 and served
two years in prison.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-08-03-98 2357EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
